Time to build the model.

# start to build model
# now we create our embedding layers
# reduce dimensionality to 50

# create input and embeddings for products
prod_input <- layer_input(shape = 1, name = "prod_input")
prod_embed <- layer_embedding(input_dim = length(unique(samp$prod_num))+1, output_dim =  50, name = "prod_embed",
                              prod_input)
prod_vec <- layer_flatten(prod_embed, name = "prod_flatten")

# do the same for customers
athlete_input <- layer_input(shape = 1, name = "athlete_input")
athlete_embed <- layer_embedding(input_dim = length(unique(samp$cust_num))+1, output_dim =  50, name = "athlete_embed",
                                 athlete_input)
athlete_vec <- layer_flatten(athlete_embed, name = "athlete_flatten")

# use dot product
prod <- layer_dot(list(prod_vec, athlete_vec), name = "dot", axes = 1) 

# keras model
mod <- keras_model(list(prod_input, athlete_input), 
                     prod)
mod %>% compile('adam', 'mean_squared_error')

# function to return most similar n products
get_sim_prod_samp = function(prod_id, n = 5, mat = samp_embed_matrix){
  # use cosine similarity 
  recs <- text2vec::sim2(mat, mat[which(rownames(mat) == prod_id),
                                                  ,drop = FALSE]) %>% 
  as.data.frame() %>% 
  tibble::rownames_to_column("rec_prod") %>% 
  mutate("og_prod" = rep(prod_id, nrow(mat)))
  colnames(recs)[2] <- c("similarity")
  recs <- recs %>% arrange(desc(similarity)) %>% 
    slice(2:(n+1)) %>% 
    select(og_prod, rec_prod, similarity)
  return(recs)
}

# create 2-D visualization of embeddings
# see if clusters are consistent with categorization
embed_plot = function(df = samp, embed_mat = samp_embed_matrix,
                      num_embed = 500){
  # use top n items in visualization
  top_df <- df %>% group_by(prod_num) %>% 
  tally() %>% 
  arrange(desc(n)) %>% 
  slice(1:num_embed)
  embed_mat <- embed_mat[which(rownames(embed_mat) %in% top_df$prod_num),]
  # use tsne 
  tsne <- Rtsne(embed_mat[1:num_embed,], perplexity = 50, pca = TRUE)
  visual_df <- tsne$Y %>% 
    as.data.frame() %>% 
    mutate(prod_num = as.integer(rownames(embed_mat)[1:num_embed]))
  visual_df <- visual_df %>% 
    inner_join(df, by = "prod_num") %>%
    mutate(category_desc = factor(category_desc))
  
  # create plot, color by category
  custom_cols <- colorRampPalette(c("red", "blue",
  "green", "orange", "violet"))(length(unique(visual_df$category_desc)))
  ggplot(data = visual_df, aes(x = V1, y = V2, colour = category_desc) ) +
    geom_point(size = 3) +
    theme_minimal() +
    scale_color_manual(values = custom_cols) +
    ggtitle("Visual Representation of Items by Category")
}
